  "texts": [
    "We separated reads based on methylation profiles and assembled a cyclical graph containing CCNE1 (Fig. 3J) that showed uniform coverage of reads throughout the graph (Supplementary Fig.",
    "The refined assembly graph deconvoluted the structure of the CCNE1 ecDNA (Fig. 3J) and demonstrated the ability to use the methylation state of reads to resolve highly complex assembly graphs (Fig.",
    "We applied this approach to additional ecDNA graphs and identified two tumors with a refined cyclic graph (Supplementary Fig. 3G and H) Patient 139 showed a profile with extensive MEI in the tumor and harbored a CDK6 ecDNA and KRAS BFB (Fig.",
    "The CDK6 amplicon contained a germline LINE-1 (Long interspersed nuclear element-1) and somatic insertions linking segments of sequences from multiple chromosomes, spanning CCND3, VEGFA and CDK6 in the amplicon (Fig. 3L-M, Supplementary Fig.",
    "The assembled amplicon graph contained two segments with LINE-1 sequences at a high CN (CN = 84) Fig. 2 | Landscape of amplicons in 710 EAC."
  ]
}